      "note": "Baseline fluorescence under continuous 10 mW/mm² wide-field (FITC) illumination in HeLa cells over ~2400 s (40 min; x-axis reaches 2400 s). Digitizing the orange ElectraON curve in Fig. 1h (overlay-verified against the 100/50/0% y-axis ticks) shows the baseline stays at ~100-106% throughout and ends ~102% — i.e. NO net photobleaching over 40 min, consistent with the paper's statement that ElectraON exhibited 'minimal bleaching' while pAce and Ace-mNeon2 lost 80% and 83% under identical conditions. brightnessRemaining set to 100 (negligible/no net loss); the prior stored value of 88% is not supported by the digitized curve and likely conflated ElectraON with the more-bleaching ElectraOFF (~90% at end). Not added to the photobleach[] gallery because the curve is non-monotonic (slight photoactivation rise then plateau ≥100%) and never approaches 75%.",
